
Feature                         	Interface	                    Abstract Class

State (Properties with values)	    ❌ Not allowed	                ✅ Allowed
Multiple Inheritance	            ✅ Yes (multiple interfaces)	❌ No (single class)
Constructor	                        ❌ Not allowed	                ✅ Allowed
Default Method Implementation	    ✅ Yes	                        ✅ Yes
Abstract Methods	                ✅ Yes	                        ✅ Yes


Use interfaces when you need to define behavior without state (e.g., Flyable, Driveable).
Use abstract classes when you need partial implementations and state.

